=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Overviews_Operators_ex34 ===

DESCRIPTION: A dark pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 100 Hz, featuring instant attack and percussive envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with resonant_steep_rolloff character, and spectrally sparse.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: instant
  brightness: dark
  crest_factor_db: percussive
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: sparse
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 100.0000
  harmonic_decay_rate: 2.9030
  harmonic_regularity: 0.1364
  pitch_clarity: 22.5405
  inharmonicity: 0.6032
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -14.8832
  resonance_freq: 796.7285

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Operators Example 34
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Overviews/Operators.html
// Tags: Operators, Overviews
// ---
// --- Example 34 ---
(
{
    var a, b;
    a = FSinOsc.ar(800);
    b = FSinOsc.ar(XLine.kr(200,500,5));
    ((a * a * b) - (a * b * b)) * 0.125
}.play)
